g only publicly traded since  idemitsu kosan is not listed on the nikkei  stock index or the topix  but instead in topix mid  the company is a member of the mitsubishi ufj financial group mufj keiretsu contents  history  early th century  postwar era  s and early s  showa shell merger  oil extraction and shipping  refining  petroleum  petrochemical products  intellectual property  other energy sources  advertisement and sponsorship  references  external links historyedit early th centuryedit sazō idemitsu founded idemitsu  co  idemitsu shōkai in  selling lubricant oil for nippon oil in moji northern kyushu he expanded to selling fuel oil for fishing boats in shimonoseki idemitsu supplied lubricant to the south manchuria railway after success in japan idemitsu  co expanded to manchuria china in  where the japaneseowned south manchuria railroad co ltd was a major customer of lubricant a branch was opened in dalian northeast china and idemitsu attempted to enter the chinese market that was dominated by western companies like standard oil and the asiatic petroleum company a shell subsidiary the company extended through northern china and into korea and taiwan after the japanese invasion of manchuria in  the oil trade became government controlled and idemitsu was forced to scale back instead he went into transport by oil tanker in  the headquarters were moved to tokyo and the name changed to the current idemitsu kosan kk kabushiki kaisha stock company with the japanese military expansion and united states joining the pacific war the government took control of all industries postwar eraedit after the war idemitsu kosan lost its overseas trade with the allied occupation of japan it was among the ten petroleum suppliers selected by the ministry of international trade and industry miti and cut its ties with nippon oil idemitsu began importing naphtha an intermediate oil product first from the united states and later from venezuela and iran the protectionist oil industry law 